PaymentCredential.title: PaymentCredential
PaymentCredential.description:
A general structure for representing an on-chain `Credential`.

 Credentials are always one of two kinds: a direct public/private key
 pair, or a script (native or Plutus).

StakeCredential.title: StakeCredential
StakeCredential.description:
Represent a type of object that can be represented either inline (by hash)
 or via a reference (i.e. a pointer to an on-chain location).

 This is mainly use for capturing pointers to a stake credential
 registration certificate in the case of so-called pointer addresses.

cardano/address/Address.title: Address
cardano/address/Address.description:
A Cardano `Address` typically holding one or two credential references.

 Note that legacy bootstrap addresses (a.k.a. 'Byron addresses') are
 completely excluded from Plutus contexts. Thus, from an on-chain
 perspective only exists addresses of type 00, 01, ..., 07 as detailed
 in [CIP-0019 :: Shelley Addresses](https://github.com/cardano-foundation/CIPs/tree/master/CIP-0019/#shelley-addresses).

cardano/address/Credential.title: Credential
cardano/address/Credential.description:
A general structure for representing an on-chain `Credential`.

 Credentials are always one of two kinds: a direct public/private key
 pair, or a script (native or Plutus).

cardano/transaction/OutputReference.title: OutputReference
cardano/transaction/OutputReference.description:
An `OutputReference` is a unique reference to an output on-chain. The `output_index`
 corresponds to the position in the output list of the transaction (identified by its id)
 that produced that output

oracle/datum/AggStateDatum.title: AggStateDatum
oracle/datum/AggStateDatum.description:
AggStateDatum contains an oracle feed - median taken from individual node feeds,
 an expiration timestamp marking time after which AggState can be consumed once again,
 and a created at timestamp for oracle users.

oracle/datum/OracleConfiguration.title: OracleConfiguration
oracle/datum/OracleConfiguration.description:
Immutable oracle settings.
 Rationale for immutability:
 * platform_auth_nft - oracle deployment corresponds to one unchanging "platform"
 * pause_period_length - oracle nodes will be sure that platform won't update this to a make very short interval
 * reward_dismissing_period_length - oracle nodes will be sure that platform won't update this to a make very short interval
 * fee_token - oracle nodes will be sure that platform won't update reward currency
 * reward_escrow_script_hash - oracle nodes will be sure that the reward escrow script is fair

fields.title: platform_auth_nft
fields.description: platform is authorized by providing its input with specific NFT inside the transaction

fields.title: pause_period_length
fields.description: pause period is when oracle can no longer do aggregations, but rewards can still be calculated

fields.title: reward_dismissing_period_length
fields.description: after this period rewards can be dismissed with DismissRewards redeemer

fields.title: fee_token
fields.description: oracle fees are paid using this asset, if it's None then ada is used

fields.title: reward_escrow_script_hash
fields.description:
when oracle platform removes nodes it will do a final token reward payout to this address,
 ada rewards are paid to nodes PaymentVkh, so escrow script hash can be set to ""

oracle/datum/OracleDatum.title: OracleDatum
oracle/datum/OracleDatum.description:
There are four types of oracle utxos:
 0. OracleSettings - one for each oracle,
    acts as single point of truth for oracle settings and node list.
 1. RewardAccount - one for each oracle,
    acts as single point of truth for reward distribution.
 2. RewardTransport - many for each oracle, with possibility of scaling their number on demand,
    users perform ODV aggregation with those by providing node feeds list constructed off-chain.
 3. AggState - each AggState utxo is complementary to RewardTransport, it contains the oracle feed value,
    that will be referenced by a user of a DApp.

fields.title: nodes
fields.description: list of oracle nodes, node id is its FeedVkh

fields.title: required_node_signatures_count
fields.description: distinct node signatures number that passes multisig check

fields.title: aggregation_liveness_period
fields.description: aggregation is considered live, i.e. usable by dapps during this period

fields.title: time_absolute_uncertainty
fields.description:
this is length of tx validity interval, so technically its value equals time absolute uncertainty times two,
 because we are taking tx validity interval middle as current time value

fields.title: iqr_fence_multiplier
fields.description:
see interquartile range (IQR) and Tukey fences methods for outlier detection,
 recommended value for this parameter is 150 (i.e. 1.5) or 170 in case of normal distribution

fields.title: utxo_size_safety_buffer
pause_period_started_at
fields.description: if oracle is in pause state, then this field will have a certain timestamp value

fields.title: nodes_to_rewards
fields.description:
we get oracle node id (FeedVkh) mapped to node reward amount
 if we zip together Nodes keys (i.e. pairs first elements) and this list of reward amounts

oracle/datum/RewardTransportDatum.title: RewardTransportDatum
oracle/datum/RewardTransportDatum.description:
RewardTransport utxo can be in two states:
 1. NoRewards - waiting for user to submit tx with OdvAggregate redeemer;
 2. RewardConsensusPending - waiting to calculate aggregation reward distribution
    and transfer user provided fees into RewardAccount utxo.

oracle/redeemer/MintingRedeemer.title: MintingRedeemer
oracle/redeemer/MintingRedeemer.description:
Types of actions for Oracle NFTs (protocol tokens)
 * MintToken  - Oracle start: one time mint for CoreSettings and RewardAccount; any number of mints for RewardTransport and AggState
 * ScaleToken - Scale RewardTransport and AggState UTxOs: any number of mints/burns for RewardTransport and AggState
 * BurnToken  - Oracle remove: all tokens are burned

oracle/redeemer/OracleRedeemer.title: OracleRedeemer
oracle/redeemer/OracleRedeemer.description:
Types of actions for Oracle smart contract
 * OdvAggregate - user sends on demand validation request together with oracle nodes message collected off-chain
 * CalculateRewards - nodes and platform can calculate reward consensus transferring user provided fees to reward UTxO
 * NodeCollect - oracle node collects rewards
 * PlatformCollect - oracle platform collects rewards
 * UpdateSettings - oracle platform changes consensus, timing or fee settings
 * AddNodes - oracle platform adds new nodes
 * DelNodes - oracle platform deletes nodes
 * ScaleDown - oracle platform burns RewardTransport and AggState NFTs, destroying corresponding UTxOs
 * DismissRewards - oracle platform turns RewardTransport UTxOs with pending rewards calculations into NoRewards
 * PauseOracle - oracle platform starts pause period, when nodes can still calculate disregarded rewards
 * ResumeOracle - redeemer for cancelling oracle pause, so that platform can suspend oracle operation only temporarily
 * RemoveOracle - oracle pause period ends and platform destroys all UTxOs and all NFTs

services/reward_escrow/RewardEscrowDatum.title: RewardEscrowDatum
services/reward_escrow/RewardEscrowDatum.description: Information on escrow script user and owner

fields.title: reward_issuer_nft
fields.description: policy ID - an authorization NFT minting script hash

fields.title: reward_issuer_address
fields.description: issuer will receive locked utxo ada fee to this address

fields.title: reward_receiver
fields.description: user vkh that signs tx claiming the rewards

fields.title: escrow_expiration_timestamp
fields.description: reward issuer can return unclaimed rewards after this moment in time

services/reward_escrow/RewardEscrowRedee.title: RewardEscrowRedeemer
services/reward_escrow/RewardEscrowRedee.description: Types of actions for Reward Escrow smart contract

anyOf.title: ReceiveReward
anyOf.description: User - in this context oracle node, redeems escrowed rewards

anyOf.title: ReturnToIssuer
anyOf.description: Reward issuer - in this context oracle platform, returns unclaimed rewards
